{"title":"BFG","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/BFG","type":"markdown","data":"| ) [File:BFG.png](/index.php?title=Special:Upload\\&wpDestFile=BFG.png \"File:BFG.png\") |                                                           |\n| ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Name                                                                                 | BFG                                                       |\n| Appearance                                                                           | ovoid device                                              |\n| Damage vs. small                                                                     | 1d2                                                       |\n| Damage vs. large                                                                     | 1d2                                                       |\n| To-hit bonus                                                                         | +0                                                        |\n| Weapon skill                                                                         | [firearm](/wiki/Firearm \"Firearm\")                        |\n| Size                                                                                 | [two-handed](/wiki/Two-handed \"Two-handed\")               |\n| Base price                                                                           | 3000 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\") (+10/positive enchant) |\n| Weight                                                                               | [100](/wiki/Weight \"Weight\")                              |\n| Material                                                                             | [silver](/wiki/Silver \"Silver\")                           |\n\nThe **BFG** is a [weapon](/wiki/Weapon \"Weapon\") that appears in [dNetHack](/wiki/DNetHack \"DNetHack\") and [notdNetHack](/wiki/NotdNetHack \"NotdNetHack\"). It is a type of [futuristic](/wiki/Future_tech \"Future tech\") [firearm](/wiki/Firearm \"Firearm\") that can fire any [item](/wiki/Item \"Item\") as a projectile. It is one of the many forms that [the Annulus](/wiki/The_Annulus \"The Annulus\") can take.\n\nThe BFG is huge and has a default [object material](/wiki/Object_materials_\\(dNetHack\\) \"Object materials (dNetHack)\") of [silver](/wiki/Silver \"Silver\"), and appears as an **ovoid device** when unidentified.\n\n## Generation\n\nThe BFG is not randomly generated, though it can be found in [bones](/wiki/Bones \"Bones\") files. Only [Tourists](/wiki/Tourist \"Tourist\") are capable of [wishing](/wiki/Wish \"Wish\") for a BFG.\n\nThe Paths of Law in the [Law Quest](/wiki/Law_quest_\\(dNetHack\\) \"Law quest (dNetHack)\") has a 1⁄1000 chance of contain a BFG or a [platinum wand](/wiki/Platinum_wand \"Platinum wand\") as part of the fallen clockwork war-machine wrecks, giving a roughly \\~0.4% probability of obtaining at least one BFG.\n\n## Description\n\nThe BFG has a range of 100 squares and a base firing rate of 3 projectiles per shot, with modifications depending on the ammo used: the firing rate is double for [bullets](/wiki/Bullet \"Bullet\"), increased by 1⁄2 rounded down for [shotgun shells](/wiki/Shotgun_shell \"Shotgun shell\"), and *decreased* by 1⁄2 rounded down for [rockets](/wiki/Rocket \"Rocket\").\n\n- *This page is a **[stub](/wiki/Category:Stubs \"Category:Stubs\")**. Should you wish to do so, you can contribute by [**expanding this page**.](https://nethackwiki.com/index.php?title=BFG\\&action=edit)*\n\n[![This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/5/5d/Nh343var-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<he