[silver]], and appears as an '''ovoid device''' when unidentified.\n\n==Generation==\nThe BFG is not randomly generated, though it can be found in [[bones]] files. Only [[Tourist]]s are capable of [[wish]]ing for a BFG.\n\nThe Paths of Law in the [[Law quest (dNetHack)|Law Quest]] has a {{frac|1000}} chance of contain a BFG or a [[platinum wand]] as part of the fallen clockwork war-machine wrecks, giving a roughly ~0.4% probability of obtaining at least one BFG.\n\n==Description==\nThe BFG has a range of 100 squares and a base firing rate of 3 projectiles per shot, with modifications depending on the ammo used: the firing rate is double for [[bullet]]s, increased by {{frac|2}} rounded down for [[shotgun shell]]s, and ''decreased'' by {{frac|2}} rounded down for [[rocket]]s. \n{{stub}}\n{{variant-343}}\n[[Category:dNetHack firearms]]\n[[Category:notdNetHack firearms]]\n[[Category:dNetHack future weapons]]\n[[Category:notdNetHack future weapons]]"}